        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 2:45AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 245 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 5 miles
southeast of Cass, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Cass...                           Barnes...
Redding...                        Turners Bend...
Watalula...                       Taft...
Paradise...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 AM CDT for west central
Arkansas.</instruction>
